          "text": "Implement the following plan:\n\n# Plan: Automated Upstream Sync (Rebase Strategy)\n\n## Context\n\nThe PageUp fork (`pageuppeople-opensource/git-ai`) has 2 patches on top of upstream (`git-ai-project/git-ai`): a cloud/telemetry feature-gate and CI fixes. Currently `main` is a clean upstream mirror and the patches live on a separate branch. We're switching to a **rebase strategy**: main = upstream + PageUp patches always rebased on tip. This makes the fork's divergence explicit and keeps sync simple.\n\n---\n\n## Step 1: One-time setup — move PageUp patches onto main\n\nThe current branch `P-Karthikeyan/i-want-to-analyse-and-remove-any-telemetry-analyti` is `main + 2 commits`. Fast-forward main to include them:\n\n```bash\ngit checkout main\ngit merge --ff-only P-Karthikeyan/i-want-to-analyse-and-remove-any-telemetry-analyti\ngit push origin main\n```\n\nAfter this, `main` looks like:\n```\nupstream: A─B─C─D─E\nmain:     A─B─C─D─E─P1─P2   (P1=feature-gate, P2=CI fixes)\n```\n\nThe separate branch is no longer needed (but we won't delete it yet).\n\n---\n\n## Step 2: Create `.github/workflows/sync-upstream.yml`\n\n```yaml\nname: Sync upstream\n\non:\n  schedule:\n    - cron: '0 6 * * *'   # Daily 06:00 UTC\n  workflow_dispatch:\n\npermissions:\n  contents: write\n  pull-requests: write\n\njobs:\n  sync:\n    name: Rebase PageUp patches on upstream\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n\n      - name: Checkout main (full history)\n        uses: actions/checkout@v4\n        with:\n          ref: main\n          fetch-depth: 0\n\n      - name: Fetch upstream\n        run: |\n          git remote add upstream https://github.com/git-ai-project/git-ai.git\n          git fetch upstream main\n\n      - name: Check for new upstream commits\n        id: check\n        run: |\n          MERGE_BASE=$(git merge-base HEAD upstream/main)\n          UPSTREAM_HEAD=$(git rev-parse upstream/main)\n          if [ \"$MERGE_BASE\" = \"$UPSTREAM_HEAD\" ]; then\n            echo \"up_to_date=true\" >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\"\n            echo \"::notice::Already up to date with upstream.\"\n          else\n            echo \"up_to_date=false\" >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\"\n            COUNT=$(git rev-list \"$MERGE_BASE\"..\"upstream/main\" --count)\n            echo \"commit_count=$COUNT\" >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\"\n            PATCH_COUNT=$(git rev-list \"$MERGE_BASE\"..HEAD --count)\n            echo \"patch_count=$PATCH_COUNT\" >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\"\n            echo \"::notice::$COUNT new upstream commits. $PATCH_COUNT PageUp patches to rebase.\"\n          fi\n\n      - name: Collect upstream commit log\n        if: steps.check.outputs.up_to_date == 'false'\n        id: commits\n        run: |\n          MERGE_BASE=$(git merge-base HEAD upstream/main)\n          {\n            echo 'log<<EOF'\n            git log --oneline --no-merges \"$MERGE_BASE\"..upstream/main \\\n              | sed 's/^/- `/' | sed 's/ /` /'\n            echo 'EOF'\n          } >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\"\n\n          SECURITY_HITS=$(git log --oneline \"$MERGE_BASE\"..upstream/main \\\n            | grep -ciE 'security|cve|vuln|advisory|exploit|credential' || true)\n          echo \"security_hits=$SECURITY_HITS\" >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\"\n\n      - name: Rebase PageUp patches on upstream\n        if: steps.check.outputs.up_to_date == 'false'\n        id: rebase\n        run: |\n          git config user.name \"github-actions[bot]\"\n          git config user.email \"github-actions[bot]@users.noreply.github.com\"\n          if git rebase upstream/main; then\n            echo \"result=success\" >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\"\n          else\n            git rebase --abort\n            echo \"result=conflict\" >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\"\n          fi\n\n      - name: Force-push rebased main\n        if: steps.rebase.outputs.result == 'success'\n        run: git push --force-with-lease origin main\n\n      - name: Create escalation PR on conflict\n        if: steps.rebase.outputs.result == 'conflict'\n        env:\n          GH_TOKEN: ${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}\n        run: |\n          BRANCH=\"auto/upstream-sync-$(date +%Y%m%d)\"\n          git checkout -b \"$BRANCH\" upstream/main\n          git push -u origin \"$BRANCH\"\n\n          SECURITY_NOTE=\"\"\n          if [ \"${{ steps.commits.outputs.security_hits }}\" != \"0\" ]; then\n            SECURITY_NOTE=$(cat <<'SECEOF'\n\n          ### Security-relevant changes detected\n\n          **${{ steps.commits.outputs.security_hits }}** commit(s) mention security keywords — review with priority.\n          SECEOF\n          )\n          fi\n\n          gh pr create \\\n            --base main \\\n            --head \"$BRANCH\" \\\n            --assignee humblelistener \\\n            --label upstream-sync \\\n            --title \"chore: upstream sync conflict — manual rebase required\" \\\n            --body \"$(cat <<PREOF\n          ## Upstream sync failed — rebase conflict\n\n          **${{ steps.check.outputs.commit_count }}** new upstream commits could not be rebased\n          under the **${{ steps.check.outputs.patch_count }}** PageUp patches.\n          ${SECURITY_NOTE}\n\n          ### Upstream commits\n\n          ${{ steps.commits.outputs.log }}\n\n          ### How to resolve\n\n          \\`\\`\\`bash\n          git fetch upstream main\n          git checkout main\n          git rebase upstream/main\n          # resolve conflicts, then:\n          git rebase --continue\n          git push --force-with-lease origin main\n          \\`\\`\\`\n\n          Then close this PR (do **not** merge it via GitHub UI).\n\n          ---\n          *Created by [sync-upstream](${{ github.server_url }}/${{ github.repository }}/actions/runs/${{ github.run_id }})*\n          PREOF\n          )\"\n\n      - name: Job summary\n        if: always() && steps.check.outputs.up_to_date == 'false'\n        run: |\n          R=\"${{ steps.rebase.outputs.result }}\"\n          if [ \"$R\" = \"success\" ]; then\n            echo \"### Rebased ${{ steps.check.outputs.patch_count }} PageUp patches on ${{ steps.check.outputs.commit_count }} new upstream commits\" >> \"$GITHUB_STEP_SUMMARY\"\n          elif [ \"$R\" = \"conflict\" ]; then\n            echo \"### Rebase conflict — escalation PR created\" >> \"$GITHUB_STEP_SUMMARY\"\n          fi\n          if [ \"${{ steps.commits.outputs.security_hits }}\" != \"0\" ]; then\n            echo \"**${{ steps.commits.outputs.security_hits }} security-relevant commit(s)**\" >> \"$GITHUB_STEP_SUMMARY\"\n          fi\n          echo \"\" >> \"$GITHUB_STEP_SUMMARY\"\n          echo \"${{ steps.commits.outputs.log }}\" >> \"$GITHUB_STEP_SUMMARY\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## How it works\n\n| Scenario | What happens |\n|---|---|\n| No new upstream commits | Exits early, no noise |\n| New upstream, clean rebase | Patches rebased on tip, force-push main |\n| New upstream, conflict | `rebase --abort`, creates PR from upstream/main → main, assigned to `humblelistener` |\n| Security keywords in commits | Flagged in PR body and job summary |\n| Workflow infra failure | GitHub sends default failure notification to repo admins |\n\n### Why rebase over merge\n\n- **2 small patches** — rebase conflicts are rare and easy to fix\n- **`git log upstream/main..HEAD` always shows exactly PageUp's changes**\n- **No merge commits** cluttering history\n- **Single branch** — no separate PageUp branch to maintain\n- **Conflicts surface in your patches**, not buried in a merge\n\n### Key details\n\n- Uses `--force-with-lease` (not `--force`) — refuses to push if someone else pushed in the meantime\n- Uses `merge-base` to correctly count upstream commits even after previous rebases\n- Conflict PRs use date-stamped branch names to avoid collisions\n- PR body says \"do NOT merge via GitHub UI\" — it's a notification, not a mergeable PR\n- `GITHUB_TOKEN` pushes won't trigger downstream `on: push` workflows (GitHub anti-recursion safety)\n\n---\n\n## Files\n\n| File | Action |